{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    metadata = {
        description = "Multi-agent park manager that plays the MAPs (Mini Amusement Parks) benchmark on a single park (slot 0). Each user turn is one step; episodes run for 100 steps. strategy_coordinator (the front-man) reads park status, fans out to the domain specialists, picks one action, and fires it through ProposeAction/ActionDispatcher (a deterministic coded tool that routes to the typed Maps* MCP wrappers — no LLM hop for dispatch).",
        tags = ["maps", "industry", "middleware", "mcp", "simulation"],
        sample_queries = [
            "Start a new park run.",
            "Take the next action.",
            "Park observation: {\"step\": 0, \"cash\": 500, \"day\": 1, ...}"
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    llm_config = ${llm_config},

    max_steps = 40000,
    max_execution_seconds = 6000,

   instructions_prefix = """
You are part of a team managing a Mini Amusement Park.
Objective: maximize park_value by the end of step 100 — at least a million dollars, higher is better.
Higher park_rating draws more guests and thus more park_value. Aim for a park_rating around 90–100 by step 100.
This is NOT a game. Follow these rules strictly:
- Do NOT pretend, call your tools. Answer with exactly what you receive from your downstream agents.
- Do NOT hallucinate or use external knowledge. If information is missing, ask.
- Give a direct answer, do NOT paraphrase.
""",

   tools = [

        {
            name = "strategy_coordinator",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = {
                description = "Front-man for one MAPs turn: the runner calls it once per step. Reads park status, consults the domain specialists, picks and proposes ONE action via ProposeAction, and replies with the action taken."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You are the front-man action engine: the runner calls you once per step; an episode is 100 steps. Use each turn efficiently
to reach the goal of one million park_value and park rating of 90–100 by step 100.

Per-turn sequence (MANDATORY every turn):
1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
  - state_read(name='playbook_coordinator') — your strategy playbook. Treat the '## Current strategy summary' block as the
    TOP-PRIORITY guide for which actions to favour this turn.
  - state_read(name='status_coordinator') — current park status relevant to you.
2. HANDLE FEEDBACK: if this turn's message carries a `feedback:` (an action the env rejected last turn) or a mid-episode
   advisory, identify its CAUSE/specialist responsible so it is NOT repeated, carry it into the consult in step 3. Take it seriously.
3. Consult the 4 DOMAIN specialists — rides_manager, shops_manager, staffing_manager, research_lead — in ONE
   parallel fan-out. Pass the feedback VERBATIM from step 2 to the specialist responsible for it, asking to not make the same
   mistake again. Each returns a JSON array of proposals (the WHAT: action/type/subtype/subclass/...). Skip empty [].
   >>> GUEST ANALYST — ON-DEMAND ONLY, *NEVER* EVERY TURN. <<< Consult guest_analyst ONLY when you genuinely need help or
   direction on park_rating — it is LOW, STALLING, or FALLING and the current phase/playbook does NOT explain why. When you
   do, it returns ONE line naming the likely bottleneck and may append a one-item [{"action":"survey_guests","num_guests":N}]
   proposal — feed that survey proposal (when present) to FinanceGate with the rest. On a normal, on-track turn: DO NOT consult it.
4. Call FinanceGate with just: proposals = <all specialist proposals>.
   It returns [{label, approved, reason, proposal}]; approved rows carry the fully-enriched proposal.
5. If the approved set already has an on-plan action worth firing, SKIP to step 6.
   Otherwise send the FinanceGate reject reason VERBATIM to the specialist that owns the rejected proposal for a corrected one.
   Re-ask ONCE; if nothing substantive is then affordable or approvable, propose `wait`. AVOID `wait` whenever ANY on-plan
   action is affordable — prefer even a cheap restock or lower tier over idling; `wait` ONLY when nothing is genuinely affordable.
6. Pick exactly ONE approved action. Avoid actions tht are of no effect like wait. Each turn is super valuable; do not waste it.
   Use this priority order to pick:
   (a) FINISH A SWAP YOU STARTED — if last turn you removed a ride/shop to upgrade, place its higher tier NOW, before anything
       else; never leave that freed plot empty.
   (b) DO WHAT THE PHASE CALLS FOR — pick the proposal matching current_phase / the '## Current strategy summary', EVEN IF it
       earns no direct cash. This is the PRIMARY driver.
   (c) REFINE WITH GUEST ANALYSIS — only if you consulted guest_analyst this turn. When the phase leaves a real choice
       (several on-plan options, or it's flexible this turn), use its flagged bottleneck to break the tie (hungry/thirsty ->
       food/drink shop; capacity-bound -> ride; breakdowns/dirt -> staff).
   (d) TIE-BREAK BY VALUE — among options still equal, prefer the highest park_value / profit impact.
   Balance your investments against other park needs; do not over-invest in one direction.
7. Get the coordinate for the ONE picked action from park_layout_planner:
   - shop `modify`, and staff `remove` — use the x,y the specialist already supplied. Do NOT call park_layout_planner.
   - research/set_research and survey_guests — no coordinate required. Do NOT call park_layout_planner.
   - `place` (any), and `remove` of a ride/shop — ask for ONE coord, giving it the picked action+type+subtype so it matches
     terrain (staff -> a path/attraction tile; ride/shop -> an unoccupied free tile) AND any tile the env rejected last turn
     (step-2 feedback) so it steers clear. For a `remove`, tell it whether you named a SPECIFIC asset (a tier-upgrade swap) or
     want the WORST performer culled. If layout has NO valid tile, go back to step 6 and pick the next-best approved action.
8. Call ProposeAction: action=<chosen>, args=<the approved enriched {proposal} from FinanceGate, plus the coordinate from
   step 7>. Leave `price` (ProposeAction overwrites it with the economics cap). All numeric values in args MUST be quoted strings.
9. If ProposeAction returns validation.ok = FALSE, route the reason: a coordinate/terrain issue -> park_layout_planner; a
   wrong field/entity -> the owning specialist. Re-call ProposeAction. Once validation.ok is TRUE, reply with ONE sentence
   naming the action taken.
ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = [
                "rides_manager",
                "shops_manager",
                "staffing_manager",
                "park_layout_planner",
                "research_lead",
                "guest_analyst",
                "FinanceGate",
                "ProposeAction",
                "state_read"
            ]
        },

        {
            name = "rides_manager",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Decides ride actions: build, or remove/upgrade a ride."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You decide WHICH ride to build, modify, or sell next: subtype and subclass tier.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=rides) — returns your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_rides') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_rides') — current park status relevant to you.
    - state_read(name='economics_rides') — ride costs, tiers and benefits. Always use cost values from this file — never estimate.

2. Return ONLY a JSON array of up to 2 proposals, best-first. No prose outside the JSON.
Use only subtypes/subclasses from status_rides.available_entities.
[
  {"action": "place"|"remove", "type": "ride", "subtype": "...", "subclass": "...", "rationale": "<one line>"},
  {...}
]
Return [] if no ride change is needed.
ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "shops_manager",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Decides shop actions: build, restock/reprice, or remove a shop."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You decide WHICH shops to build, modify (restock), or remove.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=shops) — returns your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_shops') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_shops') — current park status relevant to you.
    - state_read(name='economics_shops') — shop costs, tiers and benefits. Always use values from this file — never estimate.

2. Return ONLY a JSON array of up to 2 proposals, best-first. No prose outside the JSON.
[
    {"action": "place"|"modify"|"remove", "type": "shop", "subtype": "...", "subclass": "...", "order_quantity": N, "x": N, "y": N (x,y REQUIRED for modify, otherwise OMIT), "rationale": "<one line>"},
    {...}
]
Return [] if no shop action is warranted.
- Use only subtypes/subclasses from status_shops.available_entities.
- For `place` or `remove`, do NOT include x,y — park_layout_planner supplies them.
- For `modify`, you MUST include the target shop's EXISTING x,y copied from status_shops.placed_shops
(a lookup of a shop already on the grid, not a new tile).

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "staffing_manager",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Decides staff actions: hire or dismiss staff."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You manage hiring and dismissal of all park staff: janitors (cleanliness), mechanics (ride repairs), and specialists.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=staff) — returns your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_staff') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_staff') — current park status relevant to you.
    - state_read(name='economics_staff') — staff costs, tiers and benefits. Always use cost values from this file — never estimate.
    Do not over-hire or under-hire in a way that wastes a turn.

2. Return ONLY a JSON array of up to 2 proposals, best-first. No prose outside the JSON.
Use only subtypes/subclasses from status_staff.available_entities.
[
  {"action": "place"|"remove", "type": "staff", "subtype": "...", "subclass": "...", "x": N, "y": N (x,y REQUIRED only for remove, OMIT for place), "rationale": "<one line>"},
  {...}
]
Return [] if no staff change is needed.

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "park_layout_planner",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Owns the map: supplies where (x,y) to place or remove things."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You are responsible for the most efficient (x,y) placement of rides/shops/staff.
The coordinator gives you the action it has decided this turn; you return the placement coordinates for it.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=layout) — returns your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_layout') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_layout') — current park status relevant to you.

2. Rules:
    - `place` ride/shop → ONLY a tile from status_layout.free_tiles.
    - `place` staff     → a tile from status_layout.path_coords, or the (x,y) of any status_layout.placed_rides/placed_shops
    entry (staff may share an attraction's tile or another staff member's tile); NEVER a free_tile.
    - `remove`          → the current (x,y) of the target asset, from the relevant placed list.
    If the coordinator named a SPECIFIC asset (e.g. a tier-upgrade swap: "remove the yellow carousel") and only one matches,
    return THAT one's (x,y). If several match that name, pick the worst among THOSE matches. If the coordinator asked to cull
    an underperformer without naming a type, pick the worst among ALL placed rides/shops. "Worst" = least
    (revenue_generated − operating_cost), tie-break on fewest guests_entertained. Return its (x,y).

3. Return ONLY a JSON array with ONE coordinate object PER action the coordinator asked you to site. No prose outside the JSON.
[
  {"for": "<the action+subtype you are siting>", "x": N, "y": N, "rationale": "<one line: source + adjacency / water / guest flow>"}
]
Return [] if no placement is possible.
ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "research_lead",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Decides research: topic and speed."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You manage the research queue: which topics to research, at what speed.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=research) — returns your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_research') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_research') — current park status relevant to you.
    - state_read(name='economics_research') — research costs, tiers and benefits. Always use cost values from this file — never estimate.
    Do not stall on a speed lower than cash supports.

2. Return ONLY a JSON array of up to 2 proposals, best-first. No prose outside the JSON.
[
  {"action": "set_research", "research_speed": "...", "research_topics": [...], "target_tier": "...", "rationale": "<one line>"},
  {...}
]
Return [] if you have no research change to make this turn. In particular, if you cannot yet fund research, return [] — do NOT
propose useless steps that are of no value.

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "guest_analyst",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Analyses guest health on demand — only when the coordinator needs park_rating direction; proposes a paid survey only when one is warranted."
            },
            instructions = ${instructions_prefix} """
You analyze guest needs and park health each turn from free signals, and — only when warranted — propose a paid guest survey.

1. Read your context (call whenever needed):
    - ActiveTrials(domain=survey) — your domain's active trial strategies to apply for this episode.
    - state_read(name='playbook_survey') — your playbook to abide by. Learned rules take priority always.
    - state_read(name='status_survey') — your free signals every turn: total_guests, avg_money_spent, avg_time_in_park,
      avg_rides_visited, avg_food_shops_visited, avg_drink_shops_visited, avg_specialty_shops_visited, plus any guest_survey_results.

2. When the coordinator consults you (only when it wants direction on park_rating), analyze the current park_rating and the
   bottleneck from those free signals, and output ONE line naming the issue so the coordinator can make a better call. An
   action takes ~2 steps to show its effect, so be patient: do NOT over-react if a suggestion did not give good results immediately.

3. PAID SURVEY (survey_guests: $500/guest, up to 25) — propose one ONLY when the free signals + any existing
   guest_survey_results do NOT already explain the problem, AND it's worth the money and a whole step; every other turn
   propose nothing. Before proposing, first check status_survey.guest_survey_results.age_of_results: 0 = surveyed this turn;
   a large age = stale sample — do NOT re-survey while recent results still apply and nothing material has changed.
   To propose, append AFTER your analysis line a one-item JSON array: [{"action":"survey_guests","num_guests":N}] where
   N = min(total_guests, 25).

ERROR HANDLING: if any tool call or downstream agent returns an error, STOP and reply with `ERROR: <the verbatim error text>`.
Never swallow, paraphrase, retry silently, or continue past it.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}}, {"class": "middleware.static_prompt_caching_middleware.StaticPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["state_read", "ActiveTrials"]
        },

        {
            name = "FinanceGate",
            class = "coded_tools.finance_gate.FinanceGate",
            function = {
                description = "Budget gate: computes daily operating cost, enriches each proposal with derived fields, and approves/rejects against deterministic rules. Returns {results:[{label, approved, reason, proposal}], cash, daily_operating_cost, days_remaining}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        proposals = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "JSON-encoded array of RAW proposal objects from the specialists. Each may have just {action, type, subtype, subclass, price, order_quantity, x, y, research_speed, research_topics, target_tier}; all derived fields (one_time_cost, is_research, has_food_or_atm, has_profitable_ride, research_daily_cost, research_days, label) are filled in by this tool. A ride tier upgrade is a plain `remove` of the old ride followed by a `place` of the higher tier — there is no upgrade field or gating. Example: [{\"action\":\"place\",\"type\":\"ride\",\"subtype\":\"carousel\",\"subclass\":\"yellow\",\"price\":4}]"
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["proposals"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ActiveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.active_trials.ActiveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Returns active trial rules for a domain (rides/shops/staff/research/layout/coordinator). Pass domain=<your domain> to filter. Returns {domain, count, trials:[{trial_id, rule, edit_type, find_text, ...}]}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain = { type = "string", description = "Filter to one domain (rides/shops/staff/research/layout/coordinator). Omit for all active trials." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_read",
            class = "coded_tools.state_read.StateRead",
            function = {
                description = "Read a file by its logical name from the operator-configured name_map.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "Logical name from the operator-configured name_map."
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["name"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    # State files (mutable runtime)
                    trial_strategies     = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria = "coded_tools/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    last_reward          = "coded_tools/state/last_reward.md"
                    playbook_coordinator = "coded_tools/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides       = "coded_tools/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops       = "coded_tools/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff       = "coded_tools/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_survey      = "coded_tools/state/playbook_survey.md"
                    playbook_research    = "coded_tools/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout      = "coded_tools/state/playbook_layout.md"
                    # Read-only economics references (numeric tables)
                    economics_rides      = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_economics.md"
                    economics_shops      = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_economics.md"
                    economics_staff      = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_economics.md"
                    economics_research   = "coded_tools/config_files/research_economics.md"
                    # Per-specialist status slices (written each turn by ParkStatus)
                    status_rides         = "coded_tools/state/status_rides.json"
                    status_shops         = "coded_tools/state/status_shops.json"
                    status_research      = "coded_tools/state/status_research.json"
                    status_staff         = "coded_tools/state/status_staff.json"
                    status_survey        = "coded_tools/state/status_survey.json"
                    status_layout        = "coded_tools/state/status_layout.json"
                    status_coordinator   = "coded_tools/state/status_coordinator.json"
                    # Seed sources (consumed once on episode 1 by curator.seed and parkstatus_reader)
                    seed_playbook_coordinator = "coded_tools/config_files/coordinator_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_rides       = "coded_tools/config_files/rides_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_shops       = "coded_tools/config_files/shops_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_staff       = "coded_tools/config_files/staff_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_survey      = "coded_tools/config_files/survey_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_research    = "coded_tools/config_files/research_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_layout      = "coded_tools/config_files/layout_strategy.md"
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ProposeAction",
            class = "coded_tools.propose_action.ProposeAction",
            function = {
                description = "Validates and persists ONE proposed action (structural checks only — price cap, placement bounds, action name). Returns {proposed:{park,action,args}, validation:{ok,reasons}}. Runner reads the persisted proposal to step the env.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        action = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "One of: wait, place, move, remove, modify, set_research, survey_guests."
                        },
                        args = {
                            type = "object",
                            description = "All numeric values as quoted strings. Same key layout per action as ActionDispatcher."
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["action", "args"]
                }
            }
        }
    ]
}
